metadata.name: Pano #92
metadata.description:
'Pano' means ‘fabric’ in Portuguese.

This project is inspired by Bauhaus textile works, especially from the artists:
Ruth Hollos-Consemüller and Gunta Stolzl

15 color palettes
3 tile sizes
2 orientation
and two special features


Artwork made fully with p5.js and used p5.grain by meezwhite and Gorilla Sun
You can read more about the process in my article on Fx(text)

metadata.name: Primordial #173
metadata.description:
Primordial is a study of abstract forms. The algorithm, written in p5.js and WebGL, utilizes domain warping to create twisted fields of color and then overlays thousands of tiny lines to provide depth and texture. The outputs are chaotic but not completely formless, like a swirling mass of plasma from the early universe, or a strange proto-life form suspended in prehistoric ooze.

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

B: Toggle borders on/off

F: Fullscreen
P: Portrait
L: Landscape
S: Square

For third party license information, please see license.md

David Brice Allen
October 2022

metadata.name: Across Paper Stones #189
metadata.description:
Wherever you want to go, you'll find a path to take you there.

Each tile is made up of two deformed rectangles. One is drawn with a drifting, fragmented outline.

Over thirty color palettes are shuffled together on each output, helping form slight edges between groups.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: Geometric Transcendence #57
metadata.description:
A series inspired by my time studying Orphism and the works of Robert Delaunay.

Geometric Transcendence experiments with carefully chosen palettes & structures in conjunction with a canvas-like texture that highlights the abstract characteristics of art during the Orphism movement.


In live mode, press 's' to save hi-res png (12000 x 16000px).


Great thanks to all collectors, supporters, and the fx(hash) community.


Made with p5js
Freeimp - October 2022

metadata.name: Bifurcation Rains #66
metadata.description:
When you look at the cityscape outside the window through the glass with the raindrops, it always seems to be undecided about its choice of state and position in space. It flows and wriggles, becoming fluid, half-river, half-thought-out fantasy. 
Bifurcation diagrams are visually similar to these traces left by water on glass. We have tried to imagine a moving world, which right now is at a point of choice.

Made with love, AI and p5.js code
To save the image, press the 's' key. Enjoy!

October, 2022
Julia V & YulikolaY

metadata.name: Tezumie 1-1 #647
metadata.description:
Tezumie have found themselves in Dimension 1-1, the perfect place for an adventure!

-WARNING-
They may seem to be a cute companion to hang out in your browser, but DO NOT leave them there for extended periods.  

Side effects may include: Missing items in your household, odd behavior in pets, a strange odor, prolonged nightmares, restless leg syndrome, hearing colors, missing teeth, uncontrollable urges, existential crisis, temporary blindness, and a strong appetite for non-edible objects.

Special Thanks to the following creators for permitting traits based on their art/style/projects;

AgataPoison, Craigers , griza, iRyanBell, Jim the Bim, KilledByAPixel, Liam Egan, Littlesilver, lucky26, MarkKnol, ozzie, PersonChen, punevyr, and the creators of MIME x MIME.

-CONTROLS-
(W)-Toggle weather
(F)-Toggle frame 
(C)-Toggle cursor
(P)–Pause
(A)-Shrink
(D)-Grow
(SHIFT + S)-Save image
(SHIFT + G)-Save 4 frames that you can use to make a GIF, see “sketch.js” for further instructions.

Made in p5js.

metadata.name: IMAGINARY NEW YORK IN UKIYO-E #64
metadata.description:
In the late 19th century, the style of ukiyo-e was brought to the West and had a major impact on the techniques of Western painting.
Van Gogh, Monet, and other up-and-coming painters of the time were inspired by the Far Eastern Japan seen through Ukiyo-e and painted.
At that time, the great distance, which was a physical barrier, stirred the imagination.

Time has changed, and in the 21st century, I do not paint. I do not even use my imagination. I simply type the words "Ukiyo-e style New York while being in Japan, with a computer in hand, accessing a server in the United States.
It is as if a painter in the U.S. had been thinking of Japan in the Far East and painted a picture.

But still, what came out of it was certainly a work of art created by my own hands.

Imagination is a unique act.
Imagination is free.
Imagination does not belong to anyone.

What is imagination?


19世紀後半、浮世絵というスタイルが西洋にもたらされ、西洋絵画の手法に大きなインパクトを与えた。
ゴッホ、モネ、当時の新進気鋭の画家たちは、浮世絵から見る極東の日本に思いを馳せ、絵を描いた。
当時は距離という大きな隔たりが想像力を掻き立てた。

時は変わって21世紀、私は絵を描かない。想像力も働かせない。「浮世絵スタイルのニューヨーク」と単に文字を書くだけだ。日本にいながらコンピュータを片手にアメリカにあるサーバーにアクセスしながら。
それにもかかわらず、ニューヨークにいる人工知能が極東の日本に思いを馳せ描いたような絵が生成される。

だが依然として、そこから生まれたのは確かに私の手によって生み出された想像的なニューヨークの姿である。

想像は自由なのだ。
想像は誰のものでもない。

想像とは。

metadata.name: High Spirits! #192
metadata.description:
There’s always a time and a place to let loose, sit back, and lift those spirits! Through the ages, images of the filled cup, mug, or cocktail glass have molded the way we envision relaxation and good times. They’ve encoded an escape, a panacea, a nostalgic refuge, and a feeling that we seek — but may not find. 

So instead, let’s stay in the moment and live sip by sip, here and now. Let’s look directly into the blazing neon lights, experience something unexpected, and remember that the best drink is one shared. Cheers to all!

--------

Many pieces of High Spirits! match the community-favorite cocktails shared in the Tender Discord’s #happyhour channel… others are timeless cocktails and mocktails, defined in bold headline. Still more outputs are generative mysteries, concocted from Mr. Kislev’s Kode, open to your inventive interpretations. Enjoy the eighties electric vibes and mid-century styling, print a poster, and trade for your favorites!

--------

TENDER x Orr Kislev
September 2022
